 Some bankers said they were unaware of the alleged report that Nigerians are being defrauded through Western Union. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that Mr Ibrahim Magu, the Acting Chairman of the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC) had accused bankers of defrauding Nigerians through western union. Some of the bankers, who spoke with NAN in Abuja on Monday on condition of anonymity, said they were yet to receive such complaints about Western Union from their Nigerian customers. Continue reading ‘Western Union becoming a problem’ at Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard Mr Kelvin Okolo, the Public Relations Officer of Nigeria Union, North West Province of South Africa, says Nigerians are contributing to the growth of the area through legitimate businesses. He told newsmen in Rustenburg, North West Province of South Africa, on Friday that not all Nigerians in that country were… September 15, 2017 In "News" The Nigerian Movement for the Liberation of Western Sahara, has said it has began processes to halt the importation of sardines and other goods as part of sanctions on Morocco to end continued exploitation of the Saharawi Arab Democratic Republic. Its Coordinator, Dr Dipo Fashina, at a news conference in… September 19, 2019 In "News" The Independent Petroleum Marketers Association of Nigeria (IPMAN) has appealed to the Federal Government to re-activate the five depots in the South-West Zone to ease congestion in Apapa. Alhaji Debo Ahmed, the Chairman of South-West Zone of IPMAN, made the appeal in an interview with  Newsmen in Lagos on Tuesday. He… July 18, 2017 In "News"